        <h1>
            SW Radio Africa Syndication App
        </h1>
        <h2>
            How to syndicate a news story
        </h2>
        <ol>
            <li>For each news article you publish, go to the site: <a href="http://swradiosyndication.appspot.com/admin">http://swradiosyndication.appspot.com/admin</a></li>
            <li>Log in using the google account details provided</li>
            <li>Click the "Send URL" button</li>
            <li>Enter the URL of the SW Radio Africa News article you have just published, eg: <a href="http://www.swradioafrica.com/news150110/gpa150110.htm">http://www.swradioafrica.com/news150110/gpa150110.htm</a> and hit "Go"
            </li>
            <li>Verify that the article details have been imported correctly, and if needed modify, then hit the "syndicate" button. If you don't want the article sent to your twitter account, uncheck the button.
            </li>
            <li>The news item will be added to the RSS feed, the news site map, and (if selected) the twitter account.
            </li>
        </ol>
            <li style="list-style: none">

                <h2>
                    Twitter Account
                </h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Change settings at <a href="http://swradiosyndication.appspot.com/admin/properties">http://swradiosyndication.appspot.com/admin/properties</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <h2>
                    RSS feed
                </h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>RSS feed will be available at: <a href="http://swradiosyndication.appspot.com/rss">http://swradiosyndication.appspot.com/rss</a>
                    </li>
                    <li>Link to it by putting this in the head of all your pages:
                    </li>
                    <li style="list-style: none">
                        <code>&lt;link href="http://swradiosyndication.appspot.com/rss" rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="rss" /&gt;</code>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <h2>
                    News Site Map
                </h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Google News sitemap can be found here: <a href="http://swradiosyndication.appspot.com/newssitemap.xml">http://swradiosyndication.appspot.com/newssitemap.xml</a>
                    </li>
                    <li>(click to download and then place in the root folder of your website) eg: <a href="http://www.swradioafrica.com/newssitemap.xml">http://www.swradioafrica.com/newssitemap.xml</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
